{
  "stem": "13313.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think that deliberately they wouldn't tell his name so that I would not think if I was ever caught I would not blurt out his name.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I think it was deliberate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I can't prove that, but  that's just an afterthought.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because I would remember his name if-- if his name was given.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The-- but a couple of episodes with him are worth talking about to put things in perspective.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "That even in the worst of times, where-- your worst of enemies, there's always going-- an exception.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There's always some kind people.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So I've learned-- I learned-- learned through that to never be prejudice, never bigoted, and only to judge people on their own merit, no matter what their origin, no matter where they belong.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It completely influenced my life in terms of attitude towards other people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, as far as I'm concerned, from then on I've classified people in two categories, two categories, good people and bad people.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Because a person's identity is a matter that a person has no choice over, his origin.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Nobody chooses to be born Jewish or Christian, black or white, an Eskimo or an Aborigine in the Amazon, but everybody is in control as to how he or she behaves towards her fellow man.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And to me, that's the only yardstick that I judge people by.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "There's only two divisions, two kinds of people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And in the kind of episode, incident that brought this, that infuses in me and germinated in me and developed into my adult life.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Well, first of all, take 1943.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Incidentally, the Roggemans did have a radio, despite of the fact it was not allowed.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was hidden in some kind of cupboard and was always put on very quietly.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
